<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-166-276  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 166 276.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  April 10 1989 v6 n14 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Net upgrade disrupts MCI 800 service. (MCI Communications Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wallace, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The 50 customers who lost 800 service for up to several hoursduring the first week of April 1989 may take legal action againstMCI Communications Corp. Analysts say that the company should havewarned users that it would be updating a service-support data basebefore the failure, which affected telemarketing and customerservice operations of customers.andP;  One customer who lost servicefor several hours considered replacing MCI with ATandamp;T because MCIwas slow in responding to complaints.andP;  The new data base willprovide such 800 service enhancements as call routing by time ofday and day of week and extended call coverage.andP;  MCI experiencedan outage several days earlier as well, when an underground linesupporting 36 T-3 circuits was hit by lightning.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (services).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     FailureTelecommunicationsUpgradingCustomer RelationsSupport ServicesTelephone CompaniesNatural DisastersDisaster Management.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>